full recall of its food products following food-borne disease outbreak.Chief Executive Officer of Tiger Brands Lawrence MacDougall
says production of affected products has been halted, they have set up a
hotline to deal with customer complaints.MacDougall says Tiger Brands will be recalling the
Enterprise frankfurter, Enterprise Smoked Russians and Enterprise polony.According to Tiger Brands, there are no direct links of
deaths to their products at this moment.MacDougall told the media that they are busy with the
financial estimation of what the cost might be. He further explained that the cost of the recall out of all
the market is at Tiger Brands' expense.MacDougall said if consumers fall ill after eating their
products - they must let them know. “I can’t apologise for something I’m not clear of yet,"
MacDougall said.